This paper proposes a new algorithm for policy optimization in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper discusses the convergence rate and computational complexity of the proposed algorithm, which are topics typically studied in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates the performance of the algorithm on continuous control tasks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper discusses the non-convexity of the objective function, which is a topic studied in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed algorithm also involves stochastic optimization, which is a topic studied in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper proposes a variance reduction implementation of the algorithm, which is a topic studied in the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
